text: Imanueli Tiko (born 30 September 1974, in Lautoka) is a Fijian former rugby union player who played as wing. ==Career== He first played for Fiji on 22 May 1999, against United States, in San Francisco. Tiko was also part of the Fiji squad in the 1999 Rugby World Cup, playing two matches in the tournament. His last cap for Fiji was on 26 May 2000, against Tonga, in Nuku'alofa. ==External links== *Manu Tikomaimakogai international stats *Teivovo.com profile Category:Fiji international rugby union players Category:Fijian rugby union players Category:People from Nausori Category:Living people Category:1974 births Category:Sportspeople from Lautoka
